            "creation_date": 1596893507,
            "body": "<p>Use this function<\/p>\n<pre><code>String[] authors_arr(JSONArray authors){\n    String[] authors_res=new String[authors.length()];\n    try {\n    for(int i=0;i&lt;authors.length();i++)\n    {\n        authors_res[i]=authors.getString(i);\n    }\n    } catch (JSONException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n    return authors_res;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>call it like this <code>String[] authors_string_array = authors_arr(authors);<\/code>\nThe main point is to loop through your json array and add it into your array<\/p>\n",
